JS Ajax method in React:

1. XMLhttpRequest

issues with  XMLhttpRequest
- It is synchronous by default 
- u have to make it asynchronous explicitly
- it returns responses in text format 
- It requires explicit conversions
-It is not good in error handling 
- It is not safe as it has issues with XSRF, CORS , and XSS
            XSRF cross-site request forgery
            CORS-cross-origin  sharing 
            XSS -cross-site scripting attacks
2. js "fetch()" api  
     - fetch is a promise-based function
     - It is sync by default
     - It uses XMLHTTPRequestObject implicitly
     -It is better in error handling
 -syntax :
 fetch("url)
 .then(function(response){

 }
 .catch(function(error){
 }
 .finally(function){
 }
 )

Problems with fetch api:
- It is a DOM method 
- It is not good for the direct virtual DOM
- It returns every response in binary format 
- explicit conversion is required 
- binary conversion can be blocked by firewalls
- not very good in security like CORS , XSRF, XSS etc


Third-party library for handling AJAX requests
- Reactan uses various 3rd party libraries for handling AJAX requests
1. axios
2. whatwg-fetch
3.jQueryy Ajax [iquery-native] etc

Axios for React
- it uses XmlHttpRequest
- It is is virtual DOM library
- It is a promise-based library
- iItreturns data in native format 
- explicit conversion not required
- It is good in error handling
-It is good in security like CORS, XSRF....
- imp---> it can cancel requests
- it canhandlee multiple requestssimultaneouslyy at the same time
			https://npmjs.com
